              </p>

              <h4>The Procedure</h4>
              <ol class="procedure-steps">
                <li>Initial otoscopic examination to assess the ear canal</li>
                <li>Patient positioned comfortably with head support</li>
                <li>Microscope or endoscope positioned for optimal visualization</li>
                <li>Gentle suction applied using sterile disposable tips</li>
                <li>Wax removed in controlled sections to avoid discomfort</li>
                <li>Final examination to ensure complete removal</li>
              </ol>

              <h4>Ideal For</h4>
              <ul class="suitability-list">
                <li>Patients with perforated eardrums</li>
                <li>Those who have had ear surgery</li>
                <li>Hearing aid users</li>
                <li>People with sensitive ears</li>
                <li>Anyone wanting the safest method</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="treatment-benefits">
              <h4>Key Benefits</h4>
