              <h3>Ear Irrigation Treatment</h3>
              <p class="treatment-tagline">Gentle water-based ear cleaning</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="treatment-content">
            <div class="treatment-description">
              <h4>How It Works</h4>
              <p>
                Modern ear irrigation uses controlled water pressure and body-temperature solution to gently flush out ear wax. Unlike old-style syringing, modern irrigation equipment provides consistent, safe pressure levels with built-in safety mechanisms.
              </p>

              <h4>The Procedure</h4>
              <ol class="procedure-steps">
                <li>Pre-treatment assessment to ensure suitability</li>
                <li>Water heated to exact body temperature (37¬∞C)</li>
                <li>Gentle positioning of irrigation nozzle</li>
                <li>Controlled water flow directed along ear canal roof</li>
                <li>Wax and debris flow out naturally with water</li>
                <li>Ear dried and examined for completeness</li>
              </ol>

              <h4>Best Suited For</h4>
              <ul class="suitability-list">
                <li>Patients with intact, healthy eardrums</li>
                <li>Soft to medium consistency wax</li>
                <li>Those comfortable with water-based treatments</li>
                <li>Routine maintenance cleaning</li>
                <li>Cost-conscious patients</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="treatment-benefits">
              <h4>Key Advantages</h4>
              <div class="benefits-grid">
                <div class="benefit-item">
                  <span class="benefit-icon">üöø</span>
                  <h5>Thorough Cleaning</h5>
                  <p>Completely washes ear canal clean</p>
